messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path
- /profiles/{id}

All methods allowed?
- No

Methods allowed (based on the code)
- HEAD: No
- POST: No
- OPTIONS: No
- TRACE: No
- GET: Yes
- PUT: No
- DELETE: Yes
- PATCH: Yes

Explanation
- The main Express app mounts the profile routes at the "/profiles" prefix (index.js: app.use('/profiles', profile)).
- In routes/profile.js the route that invokes updateProfile is defined as router.patch('/:id', updateProfile). Combined with the mount prefix this yields the full path /profiles/:id; using OpenAPI style path parameter notation this is /profiles/{id}.
- The router also explicitly defines router.get('/:id', getProfile) and router.delete('/:id', deleteProfile), so GET and DELETE are explicitly implemented for the same path.
- Only the listed HTTP methods that are explicitly declared in the route files are marked "Yes". Methods not explicitly declared in the code (HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, POST for /profiles/{id}) are marked "No" because the task requires decisions based on the source code rather than framework runtime behaviors or defaults.
